Barbecues and cookouts have always been a favorite American pastime, and chances are more grills fire up on the Fourth of July than any other day of the year. The holiday commemorates the adoption of the Declaration of Independence on July 4, 1776 and is flush with patriotism, parades, fireworks...and food. Lots and lots of food!

Truth be told, no Fourth of July spread is complete without a variety of classic picnic fare, like <strong>Mrs. Marshall’s Potato Salad, Cole Slaw, Chicken Salad, BBQ,</strong> and <strong>Garden Pasta Salad</strong>. Fresh made and delicious, all of Mrs. Marshall's items are sure to be a hit at your Independence Day gathering. And since Mrs. Marshall's products are available at both Kroger and MARTIN'S, they're easy to find. Happy Fourth of July!<a href="http://ukropshomestylefoods.com/a-mrs-marshalls-fourth-of-july/mrs-marshalls-slide/" rel="attachment wp-att-1289"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1289" alt="Mrs. Marshall's Slide" src="http://ukropshomestylefoods.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Mrs.-Marshalls-Slide-500x375.jpg" width="500" height="375" /></a>

